  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies a replacement color for a single entry in a font color palette.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontPaletteOverride` specifies a replacement color for a single entry in a
font's color palette. Set <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontPaletteOverride.Index> to the
zero-based palette entry to replace and <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontPaletteOverride.Color>
to the new ARGB color value (`0xAARRGGBB` as a `uint`).

Pass an array or span of these overrides via
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments.PaletteOverrides> when cloning a typeface with
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone*>.

This is a value type; no disposal is required.

## Examples

```csharp
// Override palette entry 0 with a custom red
var override0 = new SKFontPaletteOverride
{
    Index = 0,
    Color = (uint)new SKColor(200, 30, 30, 255),
};
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    PaletteOverrides = new ReadOnlySpan<SKFontPaletteOverride>(new[] { override0 }),
};
using SKTypeface cloned = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
